reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 30, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I was hesitant to purchase because of several reviews and issues about assembly, mainly because the screws didn’t align. There is very little that is worse with a product that gives you grief when assembling because of quality issues. I had no real problems with alignment. I learned a long time ago to hand tighten until complete, unless you have no choice. The slot where the screw enters gives a little, so that’s an indication right there not to drive the screw all the way home because you might need to make adjustments. I’m not saying this had anything to do with the issues people complained about, but it’s a good practice to adopt during assembly, where possible. I did notice where the holes with the female threads were located had loose rattan, which wasn’t due to poor craftsmanship, but to allow room for the screw to pass. It is wrapped differently in theses areas. Again, I’m not saying this is how it was for those who commented about unraveling, just what my experience was. Assembly is much better, easier and faster with 2 people, especially when you need to help the pieces align. In the end, for the money, you can’t beat this product. It is a little in the small side, but I am 5’11, 230 lbs and I sit/fit comfortably. I don’t know if it’s durable, but after it’s first use I’m so satisfied that I’m going to order another set for the other side. The cushions are a little on the thin side, but even without the cushions they’re fine. After seeing and using this,?I liked it so much that I bought another set. I should have did this years ago. It’s like having another room.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 8, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Small set but comfortable!
reviews.reviewText: Warning- Amazon did a TERRIBLE job of getting this delivered safely. The box says in bold letter that is it Fragile and the delivery girl literally threw it on our step. The box was super destroyed. It didn’t seem to impact our product too much but concerning since there is glass inside. Assembly was difficult but not too terrible. A lot of the reviews said it was too small, so I attached a pic of my 90 on pitbull lab laying on it to show it’s not that bad. We have a smaller deck so this was absolutely perfect for us. The seat cushions do seem to hold water but we have found bringing them in if we knows it’s gonna rain just makes it easier. These are also replaceable. We love this set for the money we paid for it!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice set but difficult to put together.
reviews.reviewText: What probably should have been an hour-long job to assemble took me almost 4. The instructions were easy enough and finding the pieces were fine. My biggest challenge was some of the screws were far more difficult to tighten than others. While some went in easy, in less than a few minutes others took at least 20-30 minutes. I had one that I had to take out and replace but it still would not go in. Also the legs on the table were uneven. Not sure how as that was the simplest assembly of all. Overall the set does fit nicely on my small front porch. I am not sure if it will last for years, but it will work for right now until I can upgrade to something more permanent. Just waiting to get the funds to redo my front deck before investing more right now. In the end, it works and makes the porch lot nice and organized.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars 5 month after purchasing…
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. This patio set is exactly what I was looking for. I purchased it for my mom around mother’s day as a gift and it’s now the end of September. The furniture held up pretty good.Took me about 2 hours to put together. I had to call my sister to help me finish. The instructions were helpful but telling the pieces apart from each other was a bit difficult.Tip: Certain pieces belong on certain sides (left and right) but the instructions did not specify that. I had to take apart a chair due to the unclear instructions. [some pieces are slightly curved to help decipher which pieces belong on which side] Unfortunately I learned that the hard way.The furniture is great for short term use, I find that sitting in the seats for too long is a bit uncomfortable. (may purchase more comfortable patio cushions)Major downside was the shipping. The package came about 2 weeks late with no warning therefore I reported this to amazon because I was afraid I paid for a product that I would never receive. Amazon was super helpful and polite and apologized for the sellers mistake and even refunded me in full.Apparently the seller only sent a shipping label to amazon without the actual patio furniture. which caused the delay in shipping. I’ve been purchasing amazon shipped products only ever since to avoid the hassle.Overall the patio furniture is beautiful and it completed my mother’s day gift as you can see it came together beautifully & my mom loves it!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 14, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Waste of money
reviews.reviewText: This set looks better as a picture. First of all the box that it came in was destroyed in transit. So it was falling apart prior to me even opening it. Second I went to put it together and the instructions remind me of ikea instructions. The pieces of the patio furniture just removing them from the box was already falling apart. So I could imagine how soon I’d have to replace this set just from being outside. Trying to put it together the holes didn’t line up for it to be put together. The ones that I was able to get screwed together it ended up stripping the bolt so it was hard to take off since I ended up just returning it. Huge waste of time and money and to make it worse to refund it you have To carry it back to the UPS store and make sure you print off the slip cuz you’ll need that too and haul it into the store. Do yourself a favor and don’t order this. It’s not big at all for a normal sized adult and I’d tether do ikea furniture cuz at least then I can put the bolts in the holes and don’t have to worry about trying to fit something into a small ass space or trying to pull/push to make the bolt go in. 10/10 DONT RECOMMEND!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 27, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I wasn’t sure what to expect, but this was easy to assemble, sturdy, comfortable and nice looking. Less expensive than what I have seen in the store so the surprise was great. Lightweight but also sturdy and doesn’t blow away in a high wind storm. Cushion covers come off to clean, and are actually comfortable.
